.TH "gen_pool_create" 9 "gen_pool_create" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gen_pool_create \- create a new special memory pool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct gen_pool *" gen_pool_create
.BI "(int min_alloc_order "  ","
.BI "int nid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "min_alloc_order" 12
log base 2 of number of bytes each bitmap bit represents
.IP "nid" 12
node id of the node the pool structure should be allocated on, or -1
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Create a new special memory pool that can be used to manage special purpose
memory not managed by the regular kmalloc/kfree interface.
